---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import WireframeBackground from '../../components/WireframeBackground.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
---

<Layout title="AI-Powered Document Classification: Automating Compliance & Organization">
  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="relative min-h-[40vh] flex items-center justify-center wireframe-bg overflow-hidden">
      <WireframeBackground />
      <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 text-center">
        <div class="animate-slide-up">
          <p class="text-primary font-orbitron text-sm tracking-wider mb-4 matrix-text-shadow">
            AUTOMATED COMPLIANCE SOLUTIONS
          </p>
          <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl font-orbitron font-bold mb-6 text-white">
            AI-Powered Document Classification: <span class="text-primary">Automating Compliance</span> & Organization
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-white max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            Eliminate manual document sorting and ensure regulatory compliance with intelligent classification systems that understand content, context, and compliance requirements.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <article class="py-12 bg-black">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        
        <!-- Article Meta -->
        <div class="border-b border-gray-800 pb-6 mb-8">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
              <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M19 3h-1V1h-2v2H8V1H6v2H5c-1.11 0-1.99.9-1.99 2L3 19c0 1.1.89 2 2 2h14c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V5c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 16H5V8h14v11zM7 10h5v5H7z"/>
                </svg>
                January 10, 2025
              </span>
              <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M11.99 2C6.47 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.47 10 9.99 10C17.52 22 22 17.52 22 12S17.52 2 11.99 2zM12 20c-4.42 0-8-3.58-8-8s3.58-8 8-8 8 3.58 8 8-3.58 8-8 8z"/>
                  <path d="M12.5 7H11v6l5.25 3.15.75-1.23-4.5-2.67z"/>
                </svg>
                11 min read
              </span>
              <span class="bg-primary/20 text-primary px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold">
                Compliance Technology
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-black font-bold text-sm">JP</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-white font-medium">Jennifer Park</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Compliance Technology Specialist</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Hero Image -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <div style="position: relative; z-index: 999; background: #000; padding: 0; border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden;">
            <img 
              src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1556075798-4825dfaaf498?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2076&q=80" 
              alt="AI-powered document classification and intelligent automation" 
              class="w-full object-cover shadow-2xl"
              style="opacity: 1 !important; filter: none !important; background: #000 !important; display: block; position: relative; z-index: 1000; height: 160px !important;"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <!-- Inline image for compliance workflows - Right positioned, medium size -->
            <div class="float-right ml-6 mb-4 w-56" style="float: right; margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; width: 14rem; max-width: 14rem;">
              <div style="position: relative; z-index: 999; background: #000; padding: 0; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
                <img 
                  src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507925921958-8a62f3d1a50d?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1176&q=80" 
                  alt="Legal compliance documents and regulatory frameworks" 
                  class="w-full h-48 object-cover shadow-lg"
                  style="opacity: 1 !important; filter: none !important; background: #000 !important; display: block; position: relative; z-index: 1000;"
                />
              </div>
            </div>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Document classification has traditionally been one of the most time-consuming and error-prone aspects of enterprise content management. Manual classification processes result in <strong class="text-primary">15-25% misclassification rates</strong> and consume up to <strong class="text-primary">40% of information management resources</strong>, according to AIIM (Association for Intelligent Information Management) research.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
            AI-powered document classification systems have revolutionized this landscape, achieving <strong class="text-primary">95-99% accuracy rates</strong> while processing thousands of documents per minute. More importantly, these systems ensure consistent compliance with regulatory requirements and organizational policies through automated monitoring and classification.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- What is AI-Powered Document Classification -->
        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">What is AI-powered document classification?</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-8">
            <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-6">
              AI-powered document classification is an intelligent automation system that uses machine learning algorithms, natural language processing, and computer vision to automatically categorize, tag, and organize documents based on their content, structure, and compliance requirements. These systems understand document types, extract key information, and apply appropriate classifications without human intervention.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-primary border-l-4 border-primary p-6 rounded-r-xl mb-6">
              <h3 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-black mb-3">Core Classification Technologies</h3>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-black mb-2">Content Analysis</h4>
                  <ul class="text-black text-sm space-y-1">
                    <li>• Natural language understanding</li>
                    <li>• Named entity recognition</li>
                    <li>• Sentiment and tone analysis</li>
                    <li>• Topic modeling and clustering</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-black mb-2">Structure Recognition</h4>
                  <ul class="text-black text-sm space-y-1">
                    <li>• Document layout analysis</li>
                    <li>• Form field identification</li>
                    <li>• Table and chart extraction</li>
                    <li>• Header and section detection</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p class="text-white leading-relaxed">
              Unlike rule-based classification systems that require extensive manual configuration, AI-powered solutions learn from existing document patterns and adapt to new document types automatically. This capability is essential for organizations dealing with diverse document formats and evolving compliance requirements.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Benefits -->
        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Key Benefits of AI-powered document classification</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <!-- Compliance Automation -->
            <div>
              <!-- Image: Compliance and security - Left positioned, small size -->
              <div class="float-left mr-6 mb-4 w-48" style="float: left; margin-left: 1rem; margin-right: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; margin-top: 1rem; width: 12rem; max-width: 12rem; clear: left;">
                <div style="position: relative; z-index: 999; background: #000; padding: 0; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
                  <img 
                    src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563013544-824ae1b704d3?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80" 
                    alt="Cybersecurity and compliance monitoring dashboard" 
                    class="w-full h-44 object-cover shadow-lg"
                    style="opacity: 1 !important; filter: none !important; background: #000 !important; display: block; position: relative; z-index: 1000;"
                  />
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Automated Compliance & Risk Management</h3>
              <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-6">
                AI classification systems automatically identify documents containing sensitive information, apply appropriate retention policies, and flag potential compliance violations. This proactive approach significantly reduces regulatory risk and ensures consistent policy enforcement across the organization.
              </p>
              
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="bg-primary border border-primary p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-black mb-2">Regulatory Compliance Benefits</h4>
                  <ul class="text-black text-sm space-y-2">
                    <li>• <strong class="text-black">GDPR Compliance:</strong> Automatic PII identification and protection</li>
                    <li>• <strong class="text-black">HIPAA Compliance:</strong> PHI detection and secure handling</li>
                    <li>• <strong class="text-black">SOX Compliance:</strong> Financial document controls and audit trails</li>
                    <li>• <strong class="text-black">Industry Standards:</strong> Sector-specific compliance monitoring</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-black p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Risk Reduction Metrics</h4>
                  <div class="space-y-3 text-center">
                    <div>
                      <div class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">94%</div>
                      <div class="text-xs text-white">Reduction in compliance violations</div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <div class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">94%</div>
                      <div class="text-xs text-white">Reduction in time to achieve compliance</div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Operational Efficiency -->
            <div>
              
              <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Operational Efficiency & Cost Reduction</h3>
              <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Automated classification eliminates the need for manual document sorting, tagging, and filing. Organizations processing high document volumes report <strong class="text-primary">85-95% reduction in manual classification effort</strong> and <strong class="text-primary">75% faster document processing times</strong>.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-primary border border-primary p-4 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-black mb-2">SBI Life Insurance: Real-World Implementation Results</h4>
                <p class="text-black text-sm mb-3">
                  SBI Life Insurance, India's second-largest insurance company, implemented AI-powered document classification for claims processing. The system achieved remarkable improvements: <strong>83% reduction in processing time</strong> (down to 55 seconds), <strong>85% reduction in manual efforts</strong>, and <strong>80%+ accuracy</strong> in automated document processing.
                </p>
                <div class="text-center">
                  <span class="bg-black text-primary px-3 py-1 rounded-lg text-sm font-bold">
                    Verified ROI: 83% faster processing + 85% less manual work
                  </span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Quality & Consistency -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Improved Quality & Consistency</h3>
              <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
                AI systems apply classification rules consistently across all documents, eliminating the variability and subjectivity inherent in manual processes. This consistency is crucial for audit compliance, legal discovery, and knowledge management initiatives.
              </p>
              
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
                <div class="bg-black p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <div class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">99.2%</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-white">Classification consistency rate</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-black p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <div class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">Zero</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-white">Human bias in classification</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-black p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <div class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">24/7</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-white">Continuous processing capability</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Implementation Guide -->
        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">How AI-powered document classification Works / Implementation</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-6">Technical Implementation Process</h3>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">Phase 1: Data Preparation & Model Training</h4>
                <p class="text-white mb-4">
                  The implementation begins with analysis of existing document repositories to understand document types, current classification schemes, and compliance requirements. AI models are trained on representative document samples to learn organizational patterns and classification criteria.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-black p-3 rounded text-sm text-white">
                  <strong>Timeline:</strong> 2-4 weeks depending on document variety and volume
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">Phase 2: Automated Processing Pipeline</h4>
                <p class="text-white mb-4">
                  Documents are processed through multi-stage AI pipelines that extract text, analyze content, identify document types, and apply appropriate classifications. The system handles real-time processing for new documents and batch processing for existing repositories.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-white text-sm space-y-1 ml-4">
                  <li>• OCR and text extraction (99.5% accuracy)</li>
                  <li>• Content analysis and feature extraction</li>
                  <li>• Multi-label classification assignment</li>
                  <li>• Confidence scoring and exception handling</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">Phase 3: Continuous Learning & Optimization</h4>
                <p class="text-white">
                  AI models continuously improve through active learning, user feedback, and pattern recognition. The system identifies classification uncertainties and requests human review only when necessary, creating a feedback loop that enhances accuracy over time.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Compliance Features -->
          <div class="bg-black border border-primary p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-4">Advanced Compliance Features</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-3">Automatic Compliance Monitoring</h4>
                <ul class="text-white text-sm space-y-2">
                  <li>• Real-time policy violation detection</li>
                  <li>• Regulatory change impact analysis</li>
                  <li>• Automated retention schedule application</li>
                  <li>• Audit trail generation and maintenance</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-3">Security & Access Control</h4>
                <ul class="text-white text-sm space-y-2">
                  <li>• Sensitivity level auto-assignment</li>
                  <li>• Access control rule enforcement</li>
                  <li>• Data loss prevention integration</li>
                  <li>• Encryption and secure handling</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Use Cases and Examples -->
        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Use Cases and Examples</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <!-- Healthcare Compliance -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Healthcare: HIPAA Compliance Automation</h3>
              <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Healthcare organizations handle millions of documents containing Protected Health Information (PHI) that must be classified, secured, and managed according to HIPAA regulations. AI classification systems automatically identify PHI in various document types and apply appropriate security controls.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-primary border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-black mb-3">Implementation Success Story</h4>
                <p class="text-black text-sm mb-4">
                  A 15-hospital health system implemented AI document classification across 2.8 million patient records, research documents, and administrative files. The system now processes 25,000+ new documents daily while maintaining perfect HIPAA compliance.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
                  <div class="bg-black p-3 rounded">
                    <div class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">100%</div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-white">HIPAA compliance rate</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-black p-3 rounded">
                    <div class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">92%</div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-white">Reduction in classification time</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-black p-3 rounded">
                    <div class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">Zero</div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-white">Compliance violations in 18 months</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Financial Services -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Financial Services: Multi-Jurisdiction Compliance</h3>
              <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Global financial institutions must classify documents according to multiple regulatory frameworks (SEC, MiFID II, Basel III, local regulations). AI systems can simultaneously apply multiple classification schemes and identify documents requiring special handling or reporting.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-black p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-white italic mb-2">
                  "Our AI classification system automatically identifies trading documents requiring MiFID II reporting while simultaneously flagging potential Dodd-Frank implications. What used to require specialized compliance officers now happens automatically with 99.8% accuracy."
                </p>
                <p class="text-xs text-white">- Chief Compliance Officer, Global Investment Bank</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Manufacturing & IP Protection -->
            <div>
              <!-- Image: Manufacturing and IP protection - Right positioned, medium size -->
              <div class="float-right ml-6 mb-4 w-56" style="float: right; margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; width: 14rem; max-width: 14rem;">
                <div style="position: relative; z-index: 999; background: #000; padding: 0; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
                  <img 
                    src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581091226825-a6a2a5aee158?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80" 
                    alt="Manufacturing facility with automated document management systems" 
                    class="w-full h-44 object-cover shadow-lg"
                    style="opacity: 1 !important; filter: none !important; background: #000 !important; display: block; position: relative; z-index: 1000;"
                  />
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Manufacturing: Intellectual Property Protection</h3>
              <p class="text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Manufacturing companies use AI classification to protect intellectual property, manage technical documentation, and ensure trade secret compliance. The system automatically identifies confidential designs, proprietary processes, and sensitive technical information.
              </p>
              
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-primary p-4 rounded-lg text-center">
                  <div class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-black">98.7%</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-black">Accuracy in IP identification</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-primary p-4 rounded-lg text-center">
                  <div class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-black">75%</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-black">Faster processing time</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Best Practices and Tools -->
        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Best Practices and Tools</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-6">Implementation Best Practices</h3>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">1. Establish Clear Classification Taxonomies</h4>
                <p class="text-white mb-3">
                  Define comprehensive, non-overlapping classification categories that align with business processes and compliance requirements. Well-designed taxonomies improve AI accuracy by 20-30% and reduce post-implementation adjustments.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-black p-3 rounded text-sm text-white">
                  <strong>Best Practice:</strong> Start with 10-15 broad categories, then refine based on AI performance and user feedback.
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">2. Implement Confidence-Based Workflows</h4>
                <p class="text-white mb-3">
                  Configure the system to automatically handle high-confidence classifications while routing uncertain cases to human reviewers. This approach maximizes automation while maintaining quality control.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-2 text-center text-sm">
                  <div class="bg-green-900/30 p-2 rounded">
                    <div class="font-bold text-green-400">95-100%</div>
                    <div class="text-white">Auto-classify</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-yellow-900/30 p-2 rounded">
                    <div class="font-bold text-yellow-400">80-94%</div>
                    <div class="text-white">Review queue</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-red-900/30 p-2 rounded">
                    <div class="font-bold text-red-400">&lt;80%</div>
                    <div class="text-white">Manual review</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-primary p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">3. Monitor and Optimize Model Performance</h4>
                <p class="text-white">
                  Regularly assess classification accuracy, processing speed, and user satisfaction. Implement feedback loops that capture user corrections and use this data to retrain and improve AI models continuously.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Platform Comparison -->
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full bg-black border border-primary rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
              <thead class="bg-primary">
                <tr>
                  <th class="text-left p-4 font-orbitron font-bold text-white">Platform</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-4 font-orbitron font-bold text-white">Classification Accuracy</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-4 font-orbitron font-bold text-white">Compliance Features</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-4 font-orbitron font-bold text-white">Best For</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="border-t border-primary">
                  <td class="p-4 text-primary font-bold">Microsoft Purview</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">96-98%</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">Built-in compliance templates</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">Microsoft ecosystems</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-t border-primary">
                  <td class="p-4 text-primary font-bold">Google Cloud Document AI</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">95-97%</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">Custom compliance rules</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">Multi-cloud environments</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-t border-primary">
                  <td class="p-4 text-primary font-bold">AWS Textract + Comprehend</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">94-96%</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">Extensive customization</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-white">AWS-native applications</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- FAQs -->
        <section class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">FAQs</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-white mb-3">How does AI classification handle documents with multiple classification criteria?</h3>
              <p class="text-white leading-relaxed">
                Modern AI classification systems support multi-label classification, allowing documents to belong to multiple categories simultaneously. For example, a financial report might be classified as both "Financial Document" and "Confidential" while also being tagged for specific regulatory requirements. The system applies all relevant classifications with individual confidence scores.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-white mb-3">What happens when the AI system encounters completely new document types?</h3>
              <p class="text-white leading-relaxed">
                Intelligent systems use anomaly detection to identify documents that don't fit existing classification categories. These documents are flagged for human review, and the feedback is used to create new classification categories or refine existing ones. Leading platforms can adapt to new document types within 24-48 hours of initial detection.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
